



## ‚úÖ **What is cURL?**

* `curl` is a **command-line tool** used to **transfer data** to or from a server using protocols like HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, etc.
* Commonly used to test **APIs**, **download files**, and **send data**.

---

## ‚úÖ **Basic cURL Syntax**

```bash
curl [options] [URL]
```

---

## ‚úÖ **Common cURL Commands**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ **Get Request (Fetch Webpage/API)**

```bash
curl https://example.com
```

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ **Save Response to a File**

```bash
curl -o filename.html https://example.com
```

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ **Get Request with Verbose Output**

```bash
curl -v https://example.com
```

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ **Send a POST Request (Form Data)**

```bash
curl -X POST -d "username=user&password=pass" https://example.com/login
```

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ **Send a POST Request with JSON Data**

```bash
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"John","age":30}' https://example.com/api/users
```

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ **Send Headers**

```bash
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" https://example.com/api/data
```

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ **Download a File Silently**

```bash
curl -s -O https://example.com/file.zip
```

### 8Ô∏è‚É£ **Follow Redirects Automatically**

```bash
curl -L https://example.com
```

---

## ‚úÖ **cURL Options Cheat Sheet**

| Option | Description                                     |
| ------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `-X`   | Specify request method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) |
| `-d`   | Send data in POST requests                      |
| `-H`   | Add HTTP headers                                |
| `-o`   | Save output to file                             |
| `-O`   | Save file with original filename                |
| `-v`   | Verbose output (debug)                          |
| `-L`   | Follow redirects                                |
| `-s`   | Silent mode (no progress bar)                   |

---

## ‚úÖ **Example: Test API with cURL**

```bash
curl -X GET https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1
```

